$ Examples for Visual Basic for Application accessing the Windows API: Clipboard

{ Put text into the clipboard #vba-winapi-put-text-into-clipboard

  The following example tries to demonstrate how some text can be put into the → Windows/clipboard with → development/languages/VBA[VBA].

  This example needs the VBA declarations of the Windows API which can be found
→ development/languages/VBA/Win-API[here].

  gh|WinAPI-4-VBA|/examples/clipboard/put-text.bas||

  Compare with → development/languages/VBA/Useful-object-libraries/Microsoft-Forms#ms-forms-clipboard[MS Forms object library / accessing the clipboard].
  -
  See also the → development/languages/VBA/modules/Common/Clipboard[VBA module `clipboard`].

}

